					   <td>

			
			
			


<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
<tr>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">

		<table width="100%">
		<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    Smithing Guide, by a Master Smith</b></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><A href="mailto:NYY58414@aol.com">Smithaniel</a> | 
		            1/26/2000 7:20:11 PM</b></font></p>
		         <a href="guides.asp">
		         <font face="verdana" size="2">Return to guide listing.</font></a>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">Ok.... You wanna be a blacksmith... I am currently a Master (skill lvl above 100) and it took me less than a week, about 4 days. OK here's your instructions: START IN FREEPORT IF U CAN! Get lvl 4, should be pretty easy, just kill stuff in newbie area... Use all 20 practices on smithing... Get a friend or some nice high lvl person to give you 10-20pp... buy a lot of small pieces of ore, and a lot of water... Make A LOT of metal bits, and you are now well on your way to master ;o)... Buy Scaler Molds, a lot of em, and put in a metal bit, the scaler mold, and a FLASK of water, not summoned, into the forge and combine, you prolly won't be too successful until higher skill lvl. Once you are out of money and bits, get a lil more money off ppl. Some ppl are mean, some are generous, try find the generous ones.  Once Scalers become trivial, i think somewhere around skill level 40 or 50, make Skewers. Same basic concept, buy mold, put in metal bit, mold, water, in that order too, i find i fail much less if i do that...  NOTE: Skewers will take you all the way to skill lvl 115, but i assume you'd like to make some banded armor along the way... Ok well i started making banded gorgets (the easiest thing) at skill lvl 50 or 60... I lost a lot of money, cuz i failed ALOT when i hit skill 70, i failed about 50% of the time, (by the way, just put sheet metal, mold, and flask of water in forge to make banded armor, find a chart somewhere to find out how many sheets you need for each item) I recommend continuing scalers until 80 if u would like to make a profit from banded, but gorgets and wristbands aren't usually in too much demand.  You should be able to make, about 4 or 5 of the basic banded armor by now, but you will fail MISERABLY alot.  Don't try unless u have money to waste... Make scalers until 100, if u would like to make a good profit on banded, cuz u will be able to make almost all items except leggins and cloak, they will still give you some trouble... That is the way i did it, and it cost me about 200pp, but i did waste alot of money trying banded at lower skill lvls, due to false information on other smithing guides.  Well E-Mail me with comments or questions if u like... Have fun smithing... :)<BR>
<BR>
     -Smithaniel, Bristlebane Server
			<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
					</p>
			</td>
				<td>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td></tr>
