			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				actually, blacksmithing is hard at lower levels unless its a twink. therefor I would like to add how to make a twink blacksmith: make a human enchanter (look at starting stats to see reason) put as many points into int as u can and teh rest into str. Twink the char with bout 200-500pp. Give him a velium/platinum saphire necklace, 2 velium/platinum star rose quartz rings, and 2 gold saphire earings. if u chose the velium over the platinum it will be a total of +21 int and +10 str. I would then put 20 points into the skill, do metal bits until trivial, then toolboxes, then skewers. Skewers will fail a lot til bout 65-70, but it is worth it. I stopped at a skill of 90, and started on banded. I now have a skill of 96 (almost there!)
				</font>
			</td>

